  "notes_on_uncertainty": "Governorate-level 2024 displacement is the weakest geography field: PCBS gives firm pre-war populations and several combined 2023-2024 residency totals, but not a clean public five-governorate IDP matrix, so North/Gaza and Rafah are net-change estimates while Deir al-Balah and Khan Younis are left null. Strike and tonnage estimates are also uncertain because public sources mix 'airstrikes,' 'targets,' and 'air-to-ground munitions,' and official Israeli military totals are not used as priors except where independently echoed or used only as bounds. MoH death totals are reported direct deaths and do not distinguish civilian/combatant status; peer-reviewed capture-recapture and household-survey work indicates contemporaneous undercounting rather than inflation. The Lancet 186,000 figure is a scenario for direct plus indirect deaths, not an observed count, so it is treated as a high-end excess-mortality scenario rather than the central estimate."
}